The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Wednesday, February 11, 2004  KALYAN SHAH								Secretary, Publishers and Booksellers Guild																																							It is not needed, neither is it feasible. Who says people come to the fair to buy books? Many people come to the fair with no interest in books at all. But seeing so many types of books at one place arouses ones curiosity. That is the aim of the fair. The commercial aspect is also there. And every year, the footfall is increasing by about a lakh. Though unit sale of books had dropped for some years, we achieved a turnaround last year. This season, business was better than the last.
